<br>
For a guild like this to work with this setup, there has to be a lot of raids so that the casual gamer has a shot and is encouraged to log on..  Having a lot of raids takes a toll on the guild leadership though because it takes alot of time.  So when Aonodorus was leading FS, he put a lot of time into setting up raids and watching spawns and such and the guild progressed. When Aono was just overcome with RL issues and Hayley started leading, she simply didnt have the time to perform the way he did.<br>
<br>
For FS to have grown, I think they would have had to adopt a points system like ToS's where the members can bid points.  If loot is auctioned off this way, then the casual gamer has incentive to raid (because they can outbid to win things they really want), pooling of dkp is reduced (high demand items go for higher prices), and lesser items rot less often because their price would be determined by demand and not by an outdated value that had been assigned months ago. <br>
<br>
As for the personality conflicts, well, I cant comment on them.  I try to keep friendships in the game and nothing more.  Anything else is just asking for trouble, imo.  Its a game after all, not a dating service.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nandarie>Nandarie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:orange;'>Tavern Resident</span></span><br>  Posts: 3006<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(5/22/03 12:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3262.topic&index=76>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.mwscomp.com/movies/grail/jpgs/timencha.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: bla</span><hr size=1> but i am an ass... <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=205399"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/vicour1/NandSig.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
