<br>
Either hardcore raiders outbid casual players on the top items and casual players are forced to bid on lower end gear just to get some improvements, resulting in very well geared hardcore players and sub to moderately geared casual players.<br>
<br>
Or casual players save up their points to buy some uber item and completely ignore their overall gear, resulting in rotting gear and even more poorly equiped casual members.<br>
<br>
Some might say 'So what, the heavy raiders should get the good loot.', but the problem comes when you actually rely upon your casual players to succeed, poorly equiped people just don't have as much to contribute.<br>
<br>
Bidding is one of the ideas I pitched to prevent that, but it just seemed like that would make handing out loot too time consuming. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5948">Duke Krazaak Crushbone</a><br>
